caption: A church is shown with a domed roof and dramatic spires

In the photo you can see a huge cathedral of Gothic architecture in the middle of what appears to be trees, or an elaborate garden. The colors of the cathedral range from ivory to light emerald, without becoming intense. Although it is not done directly incapié, the photo frames the roof of the cathedral.

A vintage church building is shown. The building is created out of square tan colored stone with rectangular brick accenting each layer of stone. The church building is constructed on a tiled floor in a lighter tan color. Portions of the roof are flat and there are separated domed, arched sections that are made in varying levels. Three of these sections have large, bright golden crosses on top of them. There are no visible windows but there are sections that contain five small, round holes that may be a window of some type
